MBOMBELA - A memorial service for the late Ray Phiri will take place in Mbombela, Mpumalanga next Thursday.The music legend will be buried during a special provincial funeral two days later.WATCH: South Africans pay tribute to Ray PhiriPhiri died in hospital on Wednesday after losing his battle with cancer.Tributes continue to stream in for the 70-year-old music icon, whose career spanned four decades.Phiri was the founder of Stimela, with whom he conceived gold and platinum-selling albums like Fire, Passion and Ecstacy, and Look, Listen and Decide.eNCA